&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ward environment support worker&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full time hours&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Wards J84, J93, J96 and J98&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic and hardworking individuals to join the Oncology CSU as ward environment support workers. This role is essential to the smooth running of our wards and the post holder will be expected to carry out a wide range of non-clinical duties, working closely with the multi-disciplinary team in each area. Some of the core duties of the role will include cleaning of patient equipment, transportation of samples and other urgent items, ordering and managing stock levels, supporting patient flow and any other general duties that are required. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The wards in the Oncology CSU care for patients who are admitted to hospital for cancer treatment or with complications related to their cancer. We have opportunities for ward environment support workers on ward J84 (thoracic surgery), wards J93 and J96 (our medical oncology wards) and ward J98 (gynae-oncology surgery). These are busy, fast paced areas with ward teams who strive to deliver a high standard of care - if you feel ready for the challenge and would like to know more about the role please contact the ward sisters below for an informal discussion:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;J84 - Sister Tatch Dlamini 0113 2069184&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;J93 - Sister Sara Muckle 0113 2069193&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;J96 - Sister Katie Sweeting 0113 2069196&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;J98 - Sister Christine Patterson 0113 2069198 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please read the job description contained within the advert closely to make sure you have met all the essential criteria before applying.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
